Hi,

I just found that the hitbox of TextField is completely wrong.

Take this sample code, use cocos 3.6 (or 3.7):

```
    auto createTextField = [](const std::string placeHolder, const std::string text) -> Node*
    {
        auto fieldSize = Size(600,100);
        auto tf = ui::TextField::create(placeHolder, "fonts/arial.ttf", 44);
        auto bg = LayerColor::create(Color4B::RED, fieldSize.width, fieldSize.height);
        tf->setAnchorPoint(Vec2::ANCHOR_MIDDLE);
        tf->setPosition(fieldSize / 2);
        tf->setTextColor(Color4B::BLUE);
        tf->setTextHorizontalAlignment(TextHAlignment::CENTER);
        tf->setTouchAreaEnabled(true);
        tf->setTouchSize(fieldSize);
        tf->setString(text);
        bg->addChild(tf);
        return bg;
    };

    auto f = createTextField("Enter your login", "");
    f->ignoreAnchorPointForPosition(false);
    f->setAnchorPoint(Vec2::ANCHOR_MIDDLE);
    f->setPosition(visibleSize / 2);
    this->addChild(f);
```

I expect the textfield to become active when I touch inside the red box (since I used `setTouchAreaEnabled` and `setTouchSize` to cover the whole Layer size). And I expect it to become inactive when I touch outside the box.

But running this sample, it **becomes active** when you touch **somewhere to the left outside** of the box, and it **doesn't** when you touch **inside it somewhere to its right**.

I quickly looked at the hitTest method and it seems it's incorrectly computing the boundingbox of the textfield when a touchArea is specified.

